4 HR____ CELEBRATING CATHERINE SARAH DAVIS ON THE OCCASION OF
5 HER 104TH BIRTHDAY CELEBRATION.
6
7 WHEREAS, heartiest felicitations are herein proudly
8 presented to Catherine Sarah Davis on the occasion of her
9 104th Birthday Celebration; and
10 WHEREAS, born April 18, 1922, in Vincent, Alabama,
11 Catherine Davis is a remarkable woman whose life reflects
12 more than a century of faith, perseverance, and service; the
13 beloved daughter of Dera and Ernest Hamilton, she was raised
14 in an era when hard work and determination were essential;
15 from an early age, she embodied these values, laboring in
16 cotton fields at seven and later serving her family and
17 community through various employments; and
18 WHEREAS, her strong work ethic continued into
19 adulthood, exemplifying dedication and resilience; as a
20 teenager, she worked in a doctor's office performing
21 custodial duties; in her twenties, she was employed in a
22 beauty shop; in her thirties, she began a long career in
23 health care support services; she worked for 10 years at
24 Crittenton Hospital and later spent 25 years as Housekeeping
25 Supervisor at Sinai Hospital before retiring; even in
26 retirement, her commitment to service endured, as she
27 returned for three additional years at Detroit Osteopathic
28 Hospital; in later years, she devoted herself to caregiving,
Page 1

Hospital; in later years, she devoted herself to caregiving,
HR321 INTRODUCED
29 including lovingly supporting a special woman, a role she
30 regarded as a blessing; and
31 WHEREAS, faith is the cornerstone of Catherine
32 Davis's life; in 1955, she joined Mt. Olive Baptist Church,
33 where she served faithfully for more than 50 years; her
34 contributions include serving as a Deaconess, choir member,
35 and active participant in numerous ministries and church
36 boards; she was also a member of the Christian Women League
37 and served on the culinary committee, preparing meals and
38 supporting church events and fellowship; and
39 WHEREAS, her devotion and leadership were recognized
40 in 1973 when she was named Michigan Chronicle Church Woman
41 of the Year; in 2007, she was honored as a "Living Legend"
42 by Mt. Olive Baptist Church; she continues her service as a
43 member of the Mother's Board at Transformation Christian
44 Church under the leadership of Pastor Harold H. Cadwell,
45 giving all glory and praise to God for His sustaining grace;
46 and
47 WHEREAS, Catherine's life is deeply rooted in love
48 and family; on September 12, 1937, at only 15 years old, she
49 married the love of her life, Elijah Davis; their marriage
50 lasted 43 years until his passing in 1980, and she continues
51 to honor his memory with enduring love and gratitude;
52 together, they welcomed a son, Le Oscar Davis, and lovingly
53 raised a daughter, Maggie; and
54 WHEREAS, Mrs. Catherine Davis has witnessed and
55 participated in pivotal moments in American history; in
56 1963, she marched in downtown Detroit alongside Dr. Martin
Page 2

1963, she marched in downtown Detroit alongside Dr. Martin
HR321 INTRODUCED
57 Luther King, Jr. during the Civil Rights Movement, standing
58 on the front lines of the fight for justice and equality;
59 and
60 WHEREAS, beyond her work and service, Catherine is
61 known for her vibrant personality and joyful spirit; she
62 enjoys bowling and treasures memories such as getting her
63 first color television in 1950 and receiving a brand new
64 1961 black Ford LTD; her favorite color is pink, her
65 favorite Bible verse is Psalm 91, and her favorite hymn is
66 "Down Through the Years," a fitting reflection of her life's
67 journey; and
68 WHEREAS, as she celebrates 104 years, Mrs. Catherine
69 Davis stands as a living testament to strength, faith, and
70 abiding grace, inspiring all who are privileged to know her;
71 now therefore,
72 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
73 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Catherine Sarah Davis is
74 celebrated on her 104th Birthday, and this resolution is
75 offered to her in highest tribute, as well as with sincere
76 best wishes for the future.
